text_Basalt:
low in silica
dark in color
rich in iron

text_Andesite: gray to black volcanic rock with between about 52 and 63 weight percent silica (SiO2).
text_Diorite: Diorite has a coarse grain and large, interlocking crystals that are randomly oriented.

text_Peridotite: Peridotite can have a fine or coarse grain texture, and can be vitreous, pearly, or resinous in luster. It can be translucent or opaque
text_Pegmatite: Pegmatite can appear as dikes, veins, or sills, and can range in size from small patches to thousands of meters long and hundreds of meters thick.
